{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0f35f9e3-6e76-41fc-a933-36d5fed237e9","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Unsupported Target Frameworks**\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** (for .NET Core/modern .NET) and **.NET Framework 4.6.2+**. Two of your three targets are affected:\n\n| Target | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Not supported — upgrade to `net6.0` or later |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Not supported — upgrade to `net6.0` or later |\n\nBoth .NET 5.0 and .NET Core 3.1 are end-of-life and were dropped in MSTest v3.\n\n**Other changes to be aware of:**\n- **Package consolidation**: v3 offers a single `MSTest` meta-package replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n- **Breaking API changes**: Some v2 APIs were removed or renamed (e.g., changes around assertions, test lifecycle attributes).\n\n**Recommendation:** Update your `TargetFrameworks` to replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with `net6.0` (or `net8.0`) before upgrading MSTest. Would you like me to make these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"72774985-383e-4234-bea9-0baa86c8687e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project that multi-targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nKey compatibility issues with MSTest v3:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `net462` — MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2, so `net462` should still be supported. Wait, let me think more carefully. MSTest v3 minimum supported frameworks are `.NET 6.0+` and `.NET Framework 4.6.2+`. Actually, I need to be more precise.\n   \n   Looking at the actual MSTest v3 requirements, `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` are both unsupported since .NET Core 3.1 and .NET 5.0 have reached end-of-life and MSTest v3 dropped support for them. Only `net462` remains compatible.\n\n2. **Package consolidation**: MSTest v3 is consolidating its packages...\n\nActually, let me provide a clear answer about what's actually broken here.","outputTokens":782,"requestId":"6036:1FDBAC:27BDA8D:2A3859F:6A04945A"},"id":"fee85be3-acee-4595-b6a7-425139f3d9ae","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:10:34.472Z","parentId":"79c68d38-2ec0-4a97-86ce-ad8d04f88dd0"}
